returnPartialSignerBonds(uint256).notice: Returns partial signer's ETH bonds to the pool as an unbounded value. This function is called after bonds have been seized and processed by the privileged application after calling seizeSignerBonds function. It is entirely up to the application if a part of signers' bonds is returned. The application may decide for that but may also decide to seize bonds and do not return anything.
